<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Tested it again today, still the same. I might as well fess up since it's time has passed.<br>
<br>
The nerf was done to stop bards from ae kiting.<br>
<br>
Me and a few other bards on Stormhammer were pulling 60 to 70 mobs at once and ae kiting them dead in under 20mins. We were making 3 to 4 aa's a kite.<br>
<br>
The only limiting factor was the number of mobs up at once and how many you could pull before your computer got too laggy and crashed everquest.<br>
<br>
My top record was 115. (almost every pullable mob in the zone) Got almost 6 aa's on that pull.<br>
<br>
After I maxed my aa's I was doing it to powerlevel other people. Taking chars from 50 to 65 in 1 night, getting people 20 aa's in 5 hours, etc etc.<br>
<br>
It wasn't an exploit, gms watched me do it several times. But I had a feeling it wouldn't last forever.<br>
<br>
I'm curious as to how many other bards had been doing this on other servers....... <br>
Worry the Antisocial Bard<br>
